data.enText: No sugar for me, thanks─I'm counting my calories .

data.enText: a unit for measuring a quantity of heat; the amount of heat needed to raise the temperature of a gram of water by one degree Celsius

word_means: 卡(热量单位，或一克水升高1摄氏度时所需要的热量)
simple_means.memory_skill: calor 热 + ie 与…相关的物 → 卡路里

means: 千卡(测量食物含热量的单位)
卡(热量单位，或一克水升高1摄氏度时所需要的热量)

tr: unit of heat defined as the quantity of heat required to raise the temperature of 1 gram of water by 1 degree centigrade at atmospheric pressure

value.def: Calories are units used to measure the energy value of food. People who are on diets try to eat food that does not contain many calories.

example.ex: A glass of wine does have quite a lot of calories.
example.tran: 一杯葡萄酒的热量确实不低。

partsOfSpeech.dec: cale 热 + faction 形成… → 发暖（作用）
cale 热 + fy 使… → 使变暖
cal〔=cale〕热 + escence 开始出现…状态 → 逐渐增温
calor 热 + ie 与…相关的物 → 卡路里
calor 热 + ify 使… → 加热
kilo 千 + calorie 卡路里 → 大卡（热量单位）
